## 13. Recommended Maintenance Workflow

Use this process when adding or updating repository documentation:

```text
1. Identify the document category.
2. Confirm the correct folder path.
3. Check existing files for overlap.
4. Use repository naming conventions.
5. Add metadata or document header.
6. Write the document purpose.
7. Add implementation notes where applicable.
8. Add ownership notice.
9. Update this index if the file is part of the official documentation set.
10. Submit changes through pull request review.
```

---

## 14. Index Update Rule

Update this file when:

- A new major documentation file is added.
- A file path changes.
- A standard document is renamed.
- A new repository area is created.
- A new GitHub template or workflow is added.
- A document becomes deprecated.
- A release changes the official documentation structure.

